<big><big><big>'''PHENOMENON 69'''</big></big></big><br><big><big><big><big><big><big>'''Butterflies In Your Stomach'''</big></big></big></big></big></big>{{Phenomenon Class Alt|frequency=2|danger=5|scale=1|understand=1|overall=3|freqtext=The manifestations of the phenomenon are so rare that only a handful of cases are reported per year.|dangtext=Once the phenomenon manifests, survival becomes nearly impossible for the wanderer.|undertext=The exact cause, reason or origin of this phenomenon has yet to be determined.|scaletext=At any given moment, the phenomenon will manifest in only a single person.}}<big><big><big>'''OVERVIEW'''</big></big></big>

----

'''Phenomenon 69''', informally known as '''Butterflies In Your Stomach''', refers to the anomalous appearance of [[Entity 4|Deathmoths]] inside a wanderer's stomach. No pattern or direct cause has been identified, though all documented cases have involved individuals who had recently fallen in love or developed a strong romantic relationship.

The phenomenon begins without warning: a sensation resembling the expression "butterflies in the stomach," often along with a mild discomfort, nausea, or unusual movement within the abdomen, suddenly appears. Moments after, several [[Entity 4|Deathmoths]] manifest directly inside the digestive system of the affected wanderer.

In the majority of recorded cases, the [[Entity 4|Deathmoths]] are male. While still invariably fatal, male [[Entity 4|Deathmoths]] generally remain confined to the stomach, causing severe internal damage before eventually killing the wanderer.

Far rarer, however, are manifestations of the phenomenon involving female [[Entity 4|Deathmoths]]. Only a handful of such incidents have ever been documented. Unlike their male counterparts, female [[Entity 4|Deathmoths]] entirely tear open the wanderer from within due to their size.

<big><big><big>'''DOCUMENTATION'''</big></big></big>

----

The first manifestation of the phenomenon was reported on November 13<sup>th</sup>, 2005, when a woman brought her dying partner to the [[Level 4#Colonies and Outposts|S.R.C. outpost]] at [[Level 4]]. The doctors noticed strange activity in his stomach and, after an X-ray, observed multiple male specimens of [[Entity 4|Deathmoths]]. The second manifestation occurred on May 29<sup>th</sup>, 2008, and the third occurred on January 24<sup>th</sup>, 2010.

Since then, the manifestation have worryingly increased in frequency, the fourth being in March 8<sup>th</sup>, 2013 and the fifth in October 31<sup>st</sup>, 2015. Currently, five to ten documented manifestations occur annually.

As for female [[Entity 4|Deathmoths]], the first manifestation of one was on November 19<sup>th</sup>, 2017, the second one on June 28<sup>th</sup>, 2019, and the last one on June 1<sup>st</sup>, 2026. No more female [[Entity 4|Deathmoths]] manifestations have been documented so far.

<big><big><big>'''ADDENDUM'''</big></big></big>

----

A short tale written by an anonymous wanderer shortly after the first manifestation of the phenomenon went public due to [[Backrooms Today]].

<div style="max-width:900px; margin:auto; text-align:justify; line-height:1.6; font-size:15px;"><div class="titleblock">
<center><big><u>'''''Once A Happy Couple'''''</u></big></center><br>
<div style="max-width:900px; margin:auto; text-align:justify; line-height:1.6; font-size:15px;">
They were just two lovers, enjoying the peace only the [[Level 232|Field of Forgotten Forts]] could bring them. Sitting together within the interior of an abandoned fort, they shared a piece of bread while dreaming about their future.

"I'm starting to get used to this, you know?" mumbled the man with the mouth full. "At first it felt like hell, but now I kinda like it. Especially in calm levels like this."

She remained silent for a moment, a subtle smile spreading across her face. "Good. I was scared you'd leave me one day just to look for an exit," she joked. "You'd never do it, would you?"

"You sometimes tempt me to do so," he replied teasingly, grinning.

She laughed and lightly hit his shoulder.

The conversation slowly faded away, leaving only the sound of the wind hitting the walls. Through a window, she gazed at the endless grain fields beyond, letting her mind wander through them.

"I'm gonna marry him," she thought, deeply in love. "Our wedding's gonna be on [[Level 68]]."

For a while, neither of them spoke, enjoying each other's company in a warm silence, but suddenly, the man frowned.

A strange and unpleasant sensation started to spread inside his stomach. "I feel weird," he said, pressing a hand against his abdomen. "Like something's tickling my stomach from the inside."

"I told you not to eat that loaf of bread that fell on the ground earlier," she replied, handing him a glass bottle. "Drink some water. Maybe it'll help you feel better."

He took the bottle, but before he could drink, a cough escaped him, then came another, another, and another.

"Drink some water!" the woman repeated, her voice with a notable concerned tone.

He tried to answer, but violent coughing interrupted him. The worry in the woman's eyes quickly turned into terror when several jets of blood sprayed from his mouth, splattering across the floor and her hand, making the bottle slip from her hand and shatter into dozens of pieces. He collapsed moments later.

She didn't hesitate. With the adrenaline surging, she grabbed him under the arms and began dragging his body toward the nearest base. Shards of broken glass crunched under her shoes, cutting into her feet, but she ignored the pain. All that mattered was getting him help.

But as soon as they left the structure and looked up, they found themselves in a [[level 4|different place]].
</div></div></div></div></div></div>

